To correct the compilation errors in your CardServiceApplication.java file, you need to remove the extra package declarations. Here's the corrected version of your code:

```java
package com.banking.cardservice;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

@SpringBootApplication
public class CardServiceApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(CardServiceApplication.class, args);
    }
}
```

The key changes are:

1. Keep only one package declaration at the top of the file.
2. Remove the redundant package statements for org.springframework.boot and org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.

These changes will resolve the compilation errors you're experiencing. The Spring Boot dependencies are already included in your project, so you don't need to declare their packages explicitly. The @SpringBootApplication annotation takes care of the necessary auto-configuration.

After making these changes, try rebuilding your project. The compilation errors should be resolved, and your CardServiceApplication should be ready to run.

